00:14:38,608 --> 00:14:39,531
It’s okay.

275
00:15:07,721 --> 00:15:09,162
What crazy password is this?

276
00:15:09,451 --> 00:15:10,420
It’s so difficult.

277
00:15:19,841 --> 00:15:21,841
[Love you, Kang]

278
00:15:25,551 --> 00:15:26,980
[Little Brat.]
[Pain in the Neck, Argumentative]

279
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,717
You’re such a pain in the neck.

280
00:15:30,057 --> 00:15:35,000
♪ I know you don’t like if I call you my boo ♪

281
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,915
♪ Then what word can express ♪

282
00:15:39,749 --> 00:15:41,749
Damn, I’m holding my breath.

283
00:15:42,744 --> 00:15:44,744
[The contest to debut as TTM’s new artists]

284
00:15:44,865 --> 00:15:48,482
Dear all that is holy, please help us pass this round of the audition.

285
00:15:48,782 --> 00:15:49,507
Amen.

286
00:15:50,084 --> 00:15:50,627
Come on.

287
00:15:50,627 --> 00:15:51,260
Let’s find out.

288
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:51,865
I’m going to press it now.

289
00:15:52,344 --> 00:15:53,397
Let’s hold each other.

290
00:15:55,644 --> 00:15:57,396
May luck be on our side.

291
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:58,897
I pressed it.

292
00:15:58,897 --> 00:15:59,947
[Central Region: Bangkok. Nakhon Pathom, Pathum Thani]

293
00:15:59,947 --> 00:16:00,721
[Selected contestants will be contacted within today.]

294
00:16:00,721 --> 00:16:01,706
Damn!

295
00:16:03,059 --> 00:16:05,636
Why won’t they tell us who passed or not?

296
00:16:05,636 --> 00:16:06,555
Right?

297
00:16:06,555 --> 00:16:08,898
I think they want to keep it a secret for now.

298
00:16:08,898 --> 00:16:10,285
Who will they call?

299
00:16:10,819 --> 00:16:12,116
You guys, bring your phone out to standby.

300
00:16:12,116 --> 00:16:12,819
Okay.

301
00:16:16,461 --> 00:16:17,300
Potae, calm down.

302
00:16:20,091 --> 00:16:21,252
Calm down.

303
00:16:23,970 --> 00:16:25,152
Someone’s calling.

304
00:16:25,152 --> 00:16:27,100
- Answer it.
- It’s an unknown number.

305
00:16:27,923 --> 00:16:28,839
Hello?

306
00:16:30,546 --> 00:16:31,353
Yes.

307
00:16:34,749 --> 00:16:35,528
Really?

308
00:16:38,043 --> 00:16:38,815
Thank you.

309
00:16:40,107 --> 00:16:40,800
Was that TTM?

310
00:16:42,438 --> 00:16:44,257
We’re going to the next round, aren’t we?

311
00:16:44,557 --> 00:16:45,379
Yes.

312
00:16:50,062 --> 00:16:51,412
3, 2, 1.

313
00:16:55,380 --> 00:16:56,078
Hold on.

314
00:16:56,378 --> 00:16:57,790
What else did they say?

315
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,033
What do we have to do next?

316
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:01,018
They said they’ll email us the details.

317
00:17:01,018 --> 00:17:02,497
Email?

318
00:17:04,619 --> 00:17:05,252
There.

319
00:17:05,252 --> 00:17:06,111
There it is.

320
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,206
Oh, it’s the rules.

321
00:17:09,437 --> 00:17:10,160
Yeah.

322
00:17:10,486 --> 00:17:12,117
This is just general information.

323
00:17:12,344 --> 00:17:13,701
There’s nothing much.

324
00:17:13,955 --> 00:17:15,866
There’s one big problem.

325
00:17:16,374 --> 00:17:17,334
What is it?

326
00:17:17,727 --> 00:17:22,684
Contestants below 20 years old must get written permission from their parents.

327
00:17:24,091 --> 00:17:26,534
My mom made it clear that she won’t allow me to audition.

328
00:17:26,788 --> 00:17:27,956
She won’t sign the letter for me.

329
00:17:29,865 --> 00:17:30,833
What do we do?

330
00:17:31,756 --> 00:17:32,788
What now?

331
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:38,578
I have an idea.

332
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,060
There’s someone who can help me.

333
00:17:40,683 --> 00:17:41,595
Who?

334
00:17:45,151 --> 00:17:50,243
♪ I know you don’t like if I call you my boo ♪

335
00:17:51,743 --> 00:17:52,476
Kang.

336
00:17:55,305 --> 00:17:56,074
What’s up?

337
00:17:56,812 --> 00:17:58,732
You’re humming my song so early in the morning.

338
00:17:58,732 --> 00:17:59,660
Your voice is so beautiful.

339
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:01,406
I have a reward for you.

340
00:18:10,341 --> 00:18:10,994
Here.

341
00:18:11,317 --> 00:18:12,997
I saw you’ve been using your current one for a long time.

342
00:18:13,481 --> 00:18:14,704
So I brought you a new one.

343
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:16,746
Do you remember what this means?

344
00:18:20,576 --> 00:18:22,174
[Love you, Kang]

345
00:18:25,011 --> 00:18:26,839
Yes, I know what it means.

346
00:18:29,031 --> 00:18:29,966
Let me put it on you.

347
00:18:29,966 --> 00:18:30,785
Come closer.

348
00:18:33,046 --> 00:18:34,314
You look so cool and handsome.

349
00:18:34,558 --> 00:18:37,615
You’ll carry the bag on your body and my message in your heart.

350
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:41,586
Thanks.

351
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,941
Can you do me a favor instead of saying thank you?

352
00:18:44,725 --> 00:18:46,331
Will you act as my parent?

353
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,209
I passed the audition,

354
00:18:48,209 --> 00:18:49,699
but I’m not 20 yet.

355
00:18:49,814 --> 00:18:52,329
I need my parents’ permission to join the contest.

356
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:54,645
How can I be your parent?

357
00:18:54,645 --> 00:18:55,650
Ask your mom.

358
00:18:55,650 --> 00:18:57,295
My mom won’t sign it.

359
00:18:57,295 --> 00:18:59,990
I thought once your grades are good, your mom would come to understand.

360
00:18:59,990 --> 00:19:01,304
I thought so too.

361
00:19:01,489 --> 00:19:05,299
I tried to bring it up to her last night, but she cut me off.

362
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,513
Can you please help me?

363
00:19:06,513 --> 00:19:08,089
Please, Kang.

364
00:19:08,089 --> 00:19:08,887
I beg you.

365
00:19:08,887 --> 00:19:09,915
Please, Kang.

366
00:19:09,915 --> 00:19:10,769
Pretty please?

367
00:19:10,769 --> 00:19:11,389
I can’t.

368
00:19:12,335 --> 00:19:16,423
They need your parent’s signature because you’re still a minor

369
00:19:16,423 --> 00:19:18,116
and to prevent future problems.

370
00:19:18,116 --> 00:19:20,022
You need to convince your mom to sign it,

371
00:19:20,022 --> 00:19:21,319
not ask me to be your parent.

372
00:19:23,788 --> 00:19:24,582
Do you understand?

373
00:19:32,564 --> 00:19:33,377
Wait.

374
00:19:48,865 --> 00:19:50,336
Even though I can’t sign the letter for you,

375
00:19:51,213 --> 00:19:52,893
I can give you my encouragement.

376
00:19:58,782 --> 00:20:00,001
Thank you, Kang.

377
00:20:02,483 --> 00:20:03,385
I got to go.

378
00:20:03,385 --> 00:20:04,137
Okay.

379
00:20:11,361 --> 00:20:12,185
Hey, Moo.

380
00:20:12,946 --> 00:20:13,868
What brings you guys here?

381
00:20:18,728 --> 00:20:19,883
Are you okay?

382
00:20:20,829 --> 00:20:21,674
No.

383
00:20:21,674 --> 00:20:23,081
What are we going to do?

384
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,531
My mom won’t sign it.

385
00:20:25,669 --> 00:20:27,554
I’m sorry, guys.

386
00:20:27,808 --> 00:20:30,274
I don’t think I can continue this with you.

387
00:20:30,666 --> 00:20:31,990
There must be a way.

388
00:20:32,451 --> 00:20:34,649
Don’t give up yet.

389
00:20:35,712 --> 00:20:37,044
I know my mom.

390
00:20:37,205 --> 00:20:38,466
There’s no way she’s going to sign it.

391
00:20:41,050 --> 00:20:44,297
When is she visiting again?

392
00:20:44,574 --> 00:20:45,389
This Saturday.

393
00:20:45,389 --> 00:20:47,039
She’s taking me out for a meal.

394
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:47,968
Okay.

395
00:20:48,499 --> 00:20:51,223
Yos and I will persuade her.

396
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:55,089
Tae, how are you going to persuade his mom?

397
00:20:55,366 --> 00:20:56,178
Come on, Yos.

398
00:20:56,501 --> 00:20:58,635
How many girls have fallen for my words?

399
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,147
I can persuade her.

400
00:21:24,407 --> 00:21:25,368
Hi, Dad.

401
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:27,088
Are you busy?

402
00:21:28,057 --> 00:21:29,258
Are you coming home today?

403
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:33,049
I want you to sign a permission letter for me to become an idol.

404
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:35,621
I don’t think your mom and I will be home tonight.

405
00:21:35,990 --> 00:21:36,810
We have to supervise the workers.

406
00:21:36,810 --> 00:21:37,834
You can sign it yourself.

407
00:21:38,388 --> 00:21:39,233
It should be okay.

408
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:47,770
Alright.

409
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:14,285
Here’s your fried chicken with rice, Suay.

410
00:22:14,285 --> 00:22:15,584
Enjoy.

411
00:22:17,013 --> 00:22:18,044
Hey, Kang.

412
00:22:18,044 --> 00:22:19,013
Are you leaving already?

413
00:22:19,184 --> 00:22:21,626
Mom? I asked you to close for a day.

414
00:22:21,626 --> 00:22:24,560
Come on. I can run this while you’re away.

415
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,585
I’ll ask Neth to come and help.

416
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,007
Fine.

417
00:22:37,586 --> 00:22:38,415
What’s up?

418
00:22:38,876 --> 00:22:40,250
Can you come help my mom out at the restaurant?

419
00:22:42,996 --> 00:22:44,009
It’s Saturday.

420
00:22:44,332 --> 00:22:45,381
Why are you busy?

421
00:22:46,027 --> 00:22:46,819
Where are you going?

422
00:22:47,650 --> 00:22:48,817
I have something to do.

423
00:22:49,371 --> 00:22:50,184
Just come and help her

424
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:52,539
in exchange for your free food.

425
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,846
Sure, I’m available to help,

426
00:22:54,846 --> 00:22:58,476
but first, you have to tell me where you’re going, who you’re going with, and what you’re going to do.

427
00:22:58,720 --> 00:23:01,920
Are you going on a date with Moo?

428
00:23:03,954 --> 00:23:04,732
Hi, Auntie.

429
00:23:04,732 --> 00:23:06,300
Oh, hi.

430
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:07,577
Have you eaten?

431
00:23:07,687 --> 00:23:08,464
Yes.

432
00:23:08,464 --> 00:23:10,080
How are you doing? I hope you’re well.

433
00:23:10,672 --> 00:23:11,504
Who’s that?

434
00:23:11,827 --> 00:23:12,995
Talk later.

435
00:23:12,995 --> 00:23:13,904
I got to go.

436
00:23:13,904 --> 00:23:14,793
Don’t forget to come and help my mom.

437
00:23:14,793 --> 00:23:15,492
Wait, Kang.

438
00:23:17,343 --> 00:23:19,615
Can I borrow Kang to be my tour guide for a day?

439
00:23:20,561 --> 00:23:21,569
Of course.

440
00:23:21,569 --> 00:23:22,578
You’re welcome to.

441
00:23:23,039 --> 00:23:24,097
- Hi, Shone.
- Hi.

442
00:23:25,481 --> 00:23:27,822
I’m leaving then.

443
00:23:27,822 --> 00:23:29,459
Go. Don’t worry about me.

444
00:23:29,459 --> 00:23:30,688
Enjoy your trip.

445
00:23:30,688 --> 00:23:31,896
- Have a good day.
- You too.

446
00:23:31,896 --> 00:23:33,024
Neth is coming to help.

447
00:23:33,439 --> 00:23:34,654
- Alright. Don’t worry.
- Take care.

448
00:23:34,654 --> 00:23:36,224
Don’t worry. Just go.

449
00:23:38,711 --> 00:23:40,184
I knew it.

450
00:23:41,407 --> 00:23:42,974
Moo.

451
00:23:43,066 --> 00:23:43,728
Yes?

452
00:23:44,097 --> 00:23:47,840
You’re all dressed up. Are you waiting for someone?

453
00:23:49,139 --> 00:23:50,174
How do you know?

454
00:23:51,139 --> 00:23:52,336
I’m waiting for my mom.

455
00:23:54,366 --> 00:23:54,880
Your mom?

456
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:55,534
Yes.

457
00:23:56,111 --> 00:23:56,734
She’ll be here soon.

458
00:23:58,810 --> 00:24:00,086
Then who is going with Kang?

459
00:24:00,086 --> 00:24:00,646
Kang?

460
00:24:01,292 --> 00:24:03,053
No. It’s nothing.

461
00:24:04,876 --> 00:24:05,860
I got to go.

462
00:24:05,860 --> 00:24:07,123
- Bye.
- Okay. Bye.

463
00:24:09,909 --> 00:24:10,649
Kang!

464
00:24:14,802 --> 00:24:16,062
Is that Shone’s car?

465
00:24:18,216 --> 00:24:18,957
Moo.

466
00:24:20,434 --> 00:24:21,194
Oh, hi, Mom.

467
00:24:21,632 --> 00:24:22,327
You’re here.

468
00:24:22,327 --> 00:24:23,307
You’re early.

469
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:25,733
You came down to wait for me?

470
00:24:26,194 --> 00:24:27,161
Yes.

471
00:24:27,807 --> 00:24:28,742
I was waiting for you.

472
00:24:30,814 --> 00:24:31,574
Is something wrong?

473
00:24:32,814 --> 00:24:33,869
No, nothing.

474
00:24:33,869 --> 00:24:35,033
Let me help you with your stuff.

475
00:24:35,995 --> 00:24:37,326
How are you, Mom?

476
00:24:37,796 --> 00:24:39,381
Did you come from the studio or home?

477
00:24:39,381 --> 00:24:40,079
Home.

478
00:24:40,460 --> 00:24:42,968
Don’t be shocked once you enter the room.

479
00:24:43,302 --> 00:24:45,141
Why? What’s in there?

480
00:24:45,141 --> 00:24:48,266
Nothing. I just want you to prepare yourself.

481
00:24:53,484 --> 00:24:54,429
Guys.

482
00:24:54,683 --> 00:24:55,600
This is my mom.

483
00:24:59,864 --> 00:25:01,520
Hi, Mom.

484
00:25:02,339 --> 00:25:02,965
Hi.

485
00:25:03,196 --> 00:25:04,316
Hi guys.

486
00:25:08,871 --> 00:25:09,615
Sorry.

487
00:25:10,261 --> 00:25:11,794
I’m Potae.

488
00:25:11,921 --> 00:25:13,298
I’m Payos.

489
00:25:13,612 --> 00:25:15,174
We’re Moo’s best friends.

490
00:25:16,139 --> 00:25:17,298
That’s right.

491
00:25:17,506 --> 00:25:19,378
Our exam is coming up

492
00:25:19,378 --> 00:25:24,553
so I invited them to come over and study together.

493
00:25:24,727 --> 00:25:27,488
We help one another with any questions we can’t solve.

494
00:25:37,043 --> 00:25:39,920
Then I’ll come back another day.

495
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:41,466
You guys should continue studying.

496
00:25:41,627 --> 00:25:42,560
I don’t want to interrupt.

497
00:25:42,675 --> 00:25:43,659
Hold on, Mom.

498
00:25:46,312 --> 00:25:47,522
Please don’t go, Mom.

499
00:25:47,522 --> 00:25:50,240
We had no idea you were coming today.

500
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:52,811
Otherwise, we wouldn’t have come here to study today.

501
00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:54,221
We’d have come tomorrow instead.

502
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:58,444
We’re sorry, Mom.

503
00:25:59,344 --> 00:26:00,680
Please accept our apologies, Mom.

504
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:01,434
Yes.

505
00:26:02,487 --> 00:26:03,558
That’s enough.

506
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,714
You don’t need to apologize to me.

507
00:26:05,899 --> 00:26:08,512
I just wanted to visit Moo.

508
00:26:08,512 --> 00:26:10,403
I wanted to see how he’s doing

509
00:26:10,404 --> 00:26:13,465
and what kind of friends he’s hanging out with.

510
00:26:13,748 --> 00:26:19,560
But after seeing this, I…

511
00:26:22,698 --> 00:26:23,896
You feel relieved, right?

512
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,400
I think it’s a bit weird.

513
00:26:31,293 --> 00:26:32,552
How is it weird, Mom?

514
00:26:33,909 --> 00:26:36,120
I’ve never seen my son like this.

515
00:26:40,042 --> 00:26:41,226
I’ve changed.

516
00:26:41,734 --> 00:26:46,762
People change to become a better and more responsible person.

517
00:26:47,233 --> 00:26:48,034
Right, friends?

518
00:26:48,034 --> 00:26:48,841
Yes.

519
00:26:49,246 --> 00:26:51,246
Time changes, people change.

520
00:26:51,491 --> 00:26:52,477
That’s right.

521
00:26:54,346 --> 00:26:55,360
Sure.

522
00:26:55,659 --> 00:26:58,819
I won’t take any more of your study time.

523
00:27:00,342 --> 00:27:03,033
Let me go and buy some food for you to eat while you study.

524
00:27:03,656 --> 00:27:04,567
I’ll be right back, Moo.

525
00:27:04,567 --> 00:27:05,782
Please don’t be long.

526
00:27:08,297 --> 00:27:10,013
Safe trip, Mom.

527
00:27:10,290 --> 00:27:11,499
Thank you so much, Mom.

528
00:27:18,642 --> 00:27:20,959
Shall we revise chemistry next?

529
00:27:20,959 --> 00:27:22,320
Let’s do 30 practice questions.

530
00:27:26,542 --> 00:27:27,564
She’s gone.

531
00:27:29,765 --> 00:27:31,479
This place is a space for artsy kids.

532
00:27:31,479 --> 00:27:33,414
They regularly hold workshops here.

533
00:27:34,021 --> 00:27:36,021
Different kinds each week.

534
00:27:36,954 --> 00:27:40,080
Today, they’re having a ceramic workshop.

535
00:27:40,469 --> 00:27:42,240
I think you’ll get some content.

536
00:27:42,634 --> 00:27:43,418
Thank you so much.

537
00:27:51,921 --> 00:27:54,920
Press your hands down like this.

538
00:27:54,961 --> 00:27:55,590
How are you doing?

539
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:56,746
The clay is so hard.

540
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,749
I’m shaping a dish.

541
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:02,131
Wow.

542
00:28:02,774 --> 00:28:03,584
That’s beautiful.

543
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,418
Do I pull it or step on it?

544
00:28:12,558 --> 00:28:13,574
You can step on it.

545
00:28:14,128 --> 00:28:15,112
Ah.

546
00:28:16,064 --> 00:28:17,152
Yes. There you go.

547
00:28:26,528 --> 00:28:28,528
I don’t know what you guys like to eat

548
00:28:28,911 --> 00:28:30,118
so I bought a lot of things.

549
00:28:34,820 --> 00:28:39,500
Guys, before we eat, shall we recite the periodic table?

550
00:28:39,929 --> 00:28:40,684
Yes.

551
00:28:40,684 --> 00:28:42,336
That’s a very good idea, friend.

552
00:28:43,534 --> 00:28:44,120
Li?

553
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:44,766
Lithium.

554
00:28:44,766 --> 00:28:45,360
Na?

555
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:45,917
Sodium.

556
00:28:45,917 --> 00:28:46,417
K?

557
00:28:46,417 --> 00:28:46,917
Potassium.

558
00:28:46,917 --> 00:28:47,820
Rb? Rubidium.

559
00:28:47,820 --> 00:28:48,393
Cs?

560
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:49,480
What is that? I can’t remember.

561
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,047
It’s easy to memorize.

562
00:28:50,047 --> 00:28:51,379
Only two syllables.

563
00:28:51,379 --> 00:28:54,428
Remember, it starts C- with and ends with -sium.

564
00:28:54,428 --> 00:28:54,928
Oh.

565
00:28:54,928 --> 00:28:55,433
Cesium.

566
00:28:55,433 --> 00:28:56,071
Uh-huh.

567
00:28:56,235 --> 00:28:57,545
What’s Fr?

568
00:28:57,545 --> 00:28:58,657
F is for Fran.

569
00:28:58,657 --> 00:28:59,563
Fanmeet?

570
00:28:59,563 --> 00:29:00,330
Franchise.

571
00:29:00,330 --> 00:29:00,832
Francium.

572
00:29:00,832 --> 00:29:02,385
Oh!

573
00:29:02,743 --> 00:29:04,254
Studying together is worth it.

574
00:29:07,832 --> 00:29:08,552
Potae.

575
00:29:09,106 --> 00:29:09,754
Yes?

576
00:29:10,576 --> 00:29:12,586
What faculty do you want to get into?

577
00:29:13,033 --> 00:29:14,722
I want to go to a med school.

578
00:29:14,722 --> 00:29:15,687
So does Payos.

579
00:29:18,655 --> 00:29:24,840
Dream Camp For Young Aspiring Doctors.

580
00:29:27,935 --> 00:29:31,669
There’s a preparation camp coming up soon

581
00:29:31,669 --> 00:29:33,318
and Moo is interested.

582
00:29:33,481 --> 00:29:34,477
Yes, I am.

583
00:29:34,477 --> 00:29:36,240
I heard there’ll be famous tutors there.

584
00:29:37,018 --> 00:29:41,885
If a child says they want to study medicine, no parents will say no.

585
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:42,944
Oh.

586
00:29:43,552 --> 00:29:44,272
Go for it.

587
00:29:44,853 --> 00:29:45,587
That’s good.

588
00:29:45,927 --> 00:29:47,926
Just put this paper in front

589
00:29:47,926 --> 00:29:51,215
and write whatever to fill it up.

590
00:29:52,105 --> 00:29:55,660
The last page is the letter you want your mom to sign.

591
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:56,400
Right here.

592
00:29:58,009 --> 00:29:59,539
Your idea is really good, Tae.

593
00:29:59,539 --> 00:30:00,092
Yeah.

594
00:30:02,685 --> 00:30:03,751
It’s amazing.

595
00:30:04,949 --> 00:30:06,868
Could you please sign a document for me?

596
00:30:09,657 --> 00:30:10,361
Where is it?

597
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:11,783
Potae, buddy.

598
00:30:11,783 --> 00:30:12,397
Oh, yes.

599
00:30:12,397 --> 00:30:13,071
Could you pass this to her?

600
00:30:13,196 --> 00:30:14,267
Sure.

601
00:30:15,072 --> 00:30:16,088
Here it is, Mom.

602
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:19,200
But what if she reads the document?

603
00:30:19,786 --> 00:30:21,679
Come on, Moo.

604
00:30:21,679 --> 00:30:22,671
Don’t you ever watch TV dramas?

605
00:30:23,046 --> 00:30:24,722
All executives do is sign.

606
00:30:24,722 --> 00:30:25,806
I’ll act as one.

607
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:28,019
Mr. Executive, I need you to sign this document.

608
00:30:28,234 --> 00:30:29,221
Which page?

609
00:30:29,221 --> 00:30:29,728
You can just sign it here.

610
00:30:29,728 --> 00:30:30,449
Okay.

611
00:30:32,702 --> 00:30:33,638
Let me read through it first.

612
00:30:33,638 --> 00:30:35,281
(Shit. He said she wouldn’t read it.)

613
00:30:35,281 --> 00:30:36,189
Excuse me, Mom.

614
00:30:36,564 --> 00:30:39,573
Overall, it just gives you the background of the camp.

615
00:30:39,573 --> 00:30:40,705
That’s it.

616
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:44,250
But I guarantee that participants will benefit from it.

617
00:30:44,250 --> 00:30:46,220
We can confirm the benefits.

618
00:30:46,452 --> 00:30:47,976
These two have joined the camp before.

619
00:30:50,479 --> 00:30:51,765
Which page do I need to sign?

620
00:30:51,980 --> 00:30:52,583
The pen.

621
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:56,461
Here you are.

622
00:30:58,641 --> 00:30:59,169
Right here.

623
00:31:15,510 --> 00:31:16,201
Thank you.

624
00:31:16,510 --> 00:31:17,226
Thank you.

625
00:31:18,352 --> 00:31:22,232
The camp is going to be so much fun, Mom.

626
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,434
Yay.

627
00:31:25,381 --> 00:31:25,997
Alright.

628
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:27,800
Now that I’ve already signed it,

629
00:31:28,354 --> 00:31:31,227
it’s time for you to tell the truth.

630
00:31:31,996 --> 00:31:33,078
All three of you.

631
00:31:38,853 --> 00:31:39,922
What truth?

632
00:31:42,013 --> 00:31:43,119
It’s nothing.

633
00:31:43,529 --> 00:31:45,118
It’s nothing, Mom.

634
00:31:45,398 --> 00:31:48,482
Did you really think I’d believe your med school camp story?

635
00:31:50,752 --> 00:31:51,252
Hmm?

636
00:31:54,685 --> 00:31:55,336
Tell me.

637
00:32:03,381 --> 00:32:04,506
Thank you so much, Kang.

638
00:32:04,989 --> 00:32:06,051
I got a lot of footage.

639
00:32:06,051 --> 00:32:06,624
You’re welcome.

640
00:32:07,054 --> 00:32:08,137
Do you come here often?

641
00:32:08,512 --> 00:32:12,904
I used to come here a lot, but not anymore.

642
00:32:13,762 --> 00:32:14,344
Why not?

643
00:32:16,096 --> 00:32:19,986
Well, I used to come here to get tutored for art school.

644
00:32:20,308 --> 00:32:22,812
Then I quit and didn’t take the exam.

645
00:32:26,703 --> 00:32:30,419
It’s a pity you couldn’t continue in this area.

646
00:32:30,808 --> 00:32:33,240
You looked happy doing artwork.

647
00:32:36,843 --> 00:32:37,354
Shall we go?

648
00:32:37,872 --> 00:32:38,396
Yes.

649
00:32:41,973 --> 00:32:44,909
Did you think you could fool me by just wearing glasses and reading books?

650
00:32:45,696 --> 00:32:47,526
I’ve raised you for years, Moo.

651
00:32:47,794 --> 00:32:49,618
Of course, I could tell you were lying.

652
00:32:50,458 --> 00:32:53,290
You were faking it so badly.

653
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:55,220
I could tell from the first glance

654
00:32:55,631 --> 00:32:58,689
but I wanted to know how far you’d go.

655
00:32:59,249 --> 00:33:01,070
Sorry.

656
00:33:02,137 --> 00:33:02,856
Mom,

657
00:33:03,428 --> 00:33:06,380
our clip passed the audition.

658
00:33:06,684 --> 00:33:09,556
I don’t want to lose this opportunity.

659
00:33:10,128 --> 00:33:11,942
I gave you an ultimatum

660
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:15,032
but you didn’t care at all?

661
00:33:15,032 --> 00:33:16,066
I did.

662
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:19,897
I studied hard to improve my grades.

663
00:33:20,398 --> 00:33:22,328
I showed you I could do it.

664
00:33:23,883 --> 00:33:26,292
I don’t want to see you hurt again.

665
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:28,111
You’ve tried so many times.

666
00:33:28,204 --> 00:33:31,920
Every time you fail the auditions, you don't know why.

667
00:33:32,128 --> 00:33:33,324
But I do.

668
00:33:33,699 --> 00:33:35,636
I know how the industry is.

669
00:33:36,011 --> 00:33:39,574
I see you get hurt over and over again.

670
00:33:39,574 --> 00:33:41,075
Do you think that makes me feel good?

671
00:33:42,362 --> 00:33:43,280
Mom.

672
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:45,127
I really want to do this.

673
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:47,367
I want to accomplish it with my own talent.

674
00:33:47,850 --> 00:33:53,305
If I end up failing or losing, I’ll accept it.

675
00:33:54,008 --> 00:33:56,723
This time, please let me do it.

676
00:33:57,031 --> 00:33:58,103
Please give me a chance.

677
00:33:58,103 --> 00:34:02,724
Moo, I already gave you permission when I signed the letter

678
00:34:03,564 --> 00:34:06,447
because I saw that you really worked harder in school.

679
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:10,188
But

680
00:34:11,261 --> 00:34:15,113
this will be your last chance.

681
00:34:16,543 --> 00:34:18,382
If you fail this time,

682
00:34:19,949 --> 00:34:23,862
I’ll send you to live with your dad in New Zealand after you finish high school.

683
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:38,643
Today was so much fun.

684
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:39,997
See you.

685
00:34:47,903 --> 00:34:48,705
Hey, Kang.

686
00:34:49,077 --> 00:34:50,275
You’re back.

687
00:34:50,682 --> 00:34:52,320
- Yes.
- How was it? Did you have fun?

688
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:53,572
I had so much fun.

689
00:34:53,953 --> 00:34:56,378
I got to shape clay for the first time.

690
00:34:56,378 --> 00:34:58,848
At first, I thought it was going to be hard but it wasn’t at all.

691
00:34:59,150 --> 00:35:02,240
I can’t wait to see how it turns out after firing.

692
00:35:02,593 --> 00:35:04,062
I’ll get it in a few days.

693
00:35:06,776 --> 00:35:08,776
Do you want to get back to studying art?

694
00:35:13,515 --> 00:35:18,290
I know that you feel guilty about your Dad and me so you made that decision.

695
00:35:19,219 --> 00:35:20,431
But you know what?

696
00:35:21,175 --> 00:35:25,457
I feel guilty about you too for ignoring your dream.

697
00:35:29,812 --> 00:35:30,855
No, Mom.

698
00:35:31,705 --> 00:35:33,415
I made that decision on my own.

699
00:35:37,242 --> 00:35:40,259
It’s been over two years that you’ve been helping me.

700
00:35:42,782 --> 00:35:44,624
I want you to decide again.

701
00:35:46,085 --> 00:35:51,184
I want you to follow your dream and your happiness.

702
00:35:53,177 --> 00:35:55,048
I want to see you happy.

703
00:35:58,022 --> 00:35:58,752
Okay?

704
00:36:01,620 --> 00:36:02,321
Okay.

705
00:36:24,036 --> 00:36:24,771
Hello?

706
00:36:25,620 --> 00:36:26,405
It’s me.

707
00:36:26,750 --> 00:36:28,844
Oh, what’s up, Moo?

708
00:36:30,761 --> 00:36:33,292
Hey, I got the signature.

709
00:36:33,653 --> 00:36:34,777
Mom signed it for me.

710
00:36:35,081 --> 00:36:35,765
See?

711
00:36:36,376 --> 00:36:38,120
There was no need for me to act as your parent.

712
00:36:38,306 --> 00:36:38,884
You’re right.

713
00:36:39,472 --> 00:36:42,640
But where did you go today and with whom?

714
00:36:48,814 --> 00:36:49,779
How did you know?

715
00:36:50,814 --> 00:36:52,081
I saw Neth this morning.

716
00:36:52,373 --> 00:36:54,414
She thought I was going on a date with you.

717
00:36:54,653 --> 00:36:56,135
So where did you go and with whom?

718
00:36:56,719 --> 00:36:58,600
I…went to do some errands.

719
00:36:58,600 --> 00:36:59,720
What errands? With whom?

720
00:37:01,045 --> 00:37:02,449
Someone asked me to be a tour guide.

721
00:37:02,449 --> 00:37:03,231
Where?

722
00:37:03,364 --> 00:37:04,041
The art center.

723
00:37:04,041 --> 00:37:04,655
What did you do there?

724
00:37:04,655 --> 00:37:05,277
Ceramic pottery.

725
00:37:05,277 --> 00:37:06,089
Why are you angry?

726
00:37:06,089 --> 00:37:07,157
I’m not.

727
00:37:07,157 --> 00:37:08,360
Why are you making a big fuss about this?

728
00:37:08,761 --> 00:37:09,880
You nag me more than my mom.

729
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:11,240
Why haven’t you taken me there?

730
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:14,207
You’ve been to many places with me, haven’t you?

731
00:37:14,431 --> 00:37:15,609
It’s not the same.

732
00:37:15,609 --> 00:37:16,962
We’ve never dated.

733
00:37:16,962 --> 00:37:17,858
Take me on a date.

734
00:37:17,858 --> 00:37:19,904
Take me on a date and be like a couple.

735
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:21,322
We can’t be like a couple

736
00:37:23,699 --> 00:37:25,280
but we can go on a date.

737
00:37:26,088 --> 00:37:26,957
Really?

738
00:37:29,028 --> 00:37:30,159
Can we really do that?

739
00:37:30,957 --> 00:37:31,792
Just leave.

740
00:37:31,792 --> 00:37:32,612
Please stop already.

741
00:37:34,263 --> 00:37:35,404
Let me see your nails.

742
00:37:38,383 --> 00:37:39,484
Why are they so long?

743
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:40,749
I’ll take care of them.

744
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:41,522
No need.

745
00:37:41,522 --> 00:37:42,240
Kang.

746
00:37:43,090 --> 00:37:43,951
Don’t be stubborn.

747
00:37:49,661 --> 00:37:51,428
Why don’t you sit in front of me?

748
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:53,608
I’m more comfortable like this.

749
00:37:53,953 --> 00:37:54,862
This is like cutting my own nails.

750
00:38:00,122 --> 00:38:01,511
Don’t cut my skin.

751
00:38:02,397 --> 00:38:03,368
I won’t.

752
00:38:06,422 --> 00:38:07,451
By the way,

753
00:38:08,372 --> 00:38:12,072
there’s something I haven’t told you.

754
00:38:14,430 --> 00:38:16,696
My mom gave me one condition.

755
00:38:17,903 --> 00:38:21,652
If I fail the audition this time, when I finish high school,

756
00:38:23,113 --> 00:38:25,177
I’ll have to go live with my dad in New Zealand.

757
00:38:30,143 --> 00:38:31,915
I’m scared I’ll fail.

758
00:38:39,563 --> 00:38:41,417
You can do it for sure.

759
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:44,469
I’m always rooting for you here.

760
00:38:51,901 --> 00:38:52,706
Thank you.

761
00:39:02,708 --> 00:39:04,080
[New Wave Project Participation Confirmation Letter]

762
00:39:21,973 --> 00:39:23,071
Hey, bro.

763
00:39:23,682 --> 00:39:24,960
Did you call to borrow my money?

764
00:39:25,172 --> 00:39:27,255
No, Mom already gave me money.

765
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:29,695
I wanted to ask if you know the insides of the New Wave Project.

766
00:39:29,695 --> 00:39:32,921
What do they want to see in the audition?

767
00:39:32,921 --> 00:39:35,085
How many people are they looking for?

768
00:39:35,085 --> 00:39:36,083
No idea.

769
00:39:37,056 --> 00:39:39,800
So, you’re going?

770
00:39:40,542 --> 00:39:41,713
Did your mom come around?

771
00:39:41,713 --> 00:39:44,842
She did, but she gave me a harsh condition.

772
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:49,327
She said if I don’t win this, she’ll send me to live with Dad in New Zealand.

773
00:39:49,327 --> 00:39:50,370
That’s good.

774
00:39:50,503 --> 00:39:51,785
You’ll get to improve your language skills.

775
00:39:51,785 --> 00:39:53,831
I don’t want to improve my language skills.

776
00:39:54,043 --> 00:39:55,575
I want to debut here.

777
00:39:55,575 --> 00:39:59,836
Besides, the person I’m pursuing just started giving me a chance.

778
00:40:00,128 --> 00:40:02,180
Love is such a big drive in your life, huh?

779
00:40:02,180 --> 00:40:05,226
Come on. Let me see his face.

780
00:40:05,226 --> 00:40:06,042
No.

781
00:40:06,573 --> 00:40:08,077
We’re not together yet.

782
00:40:08,236 --> 00:40:10,804
Don’t steal him from me. I know what you’re trying to do.

783
00:40:10,804 --> 00:40:12,358
I’m not going to steal him from you.

784
00:40:12,358 --> 00:40:14,744
I already have eyes on someone else.

785
00:40:14,744 --> 00:40:15,630
Oh?

786
00:40:15,630 --> 00:40:16,617
Who is it?

787
00:40:16,936 --> 00:40:18,623
I’m not sure how things will go yet.

788
00:40:18,623 --> 00:40:21,058
Once I am, I’ll introduce him to you.

789
00:40:21,270 --> 00:40:22,836
Come on.

790
00:40:22,969 --> 00:40:23,811
I got to go.

791
00:40:23,811 --> 00:40:24,709
I need to edit my video.

792
00:40:24,709 --> 00:40:26,096
Okay. Bye.

