00:42:03,087 --> 00:42:05,496
♪ Oh oh eh oh o ♪

830
00:42:05,496 --> 00:42:08,052
♪ You’re the only one, ma baby ♪

831
00:42:08,052 --> 00:42:09,256
♪ Oh oh eh oh o ♪

832
00:42:12,642 --> 00:42:14,280
Kang, what are you doing here?

833
00:42:14,754 --> 00:42:16,064
Why did you turn off the music?

834
00:42:17,795 --> 00:42:18,976
You’ve practiced a lot already.

835
00:42:18,976 --> 00:42:19,795
Take some rest.

836
00:42:20,941 --> 00:42:23,074
No, I’m not dancing well enough.

837
00:42:23,724 --> 00:42:25,724
I don’t want to fail.

838
00:42:25,724 --> 00:42:26,712
You won’t.

839
00:42:26,712 --> 00:42:28,308
All this dancing is stuck in your brain by now.

840
00:42:28,517 --> 00:42:31,124
Let’s find something else to do and relax

841
00:42:31,124 --> 00:42:32,486
so you’ll feel refreshed tomorrow.

842
00:42:34,212 --> 00:42:36,106
Just the two of us?

843
00:42:36,265 --> 00:42:37,015
Yeah.

844
00:42:39,485 --> 00:42:42,000
Are you asking me on a date?

845
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:43,120
Do you want to go or not?

846
00:42:44,446 --> 00:42:45,432
Of course.

847
00:42:45,432 --> 00:42:46,040
Let’s go.

848
00:42:50,673 --> 00:42:51,903
Wow.

849
00:42:51,903 --> 00:42:53,220
This place is amazing.

850
00:42:53,220 --> 00:42:54,293
It’s nice and cool.

851
00:42:54,293 --> 00:42:55,808
I used to come here a lot.

852
00:42:56,206 --> 00:42:57,604
I loved coming here to draw.

853
00:42:58,560 --> 00:43:00,611
Yes, I remember you’re good at drawing.

854
00:43:00,903 --> 00:43:01,823
I wonder…

855
00:43:03,974 --> 00:43:05,136
Why I don’t go to university?

856
00:43:07,372 --> 00:43:08,310
Yeah.

857
00:43:09,685 --> 00:43:14,255
Actually, I planned to try for painting school two years ago.

858
00:43:14,892 --> 00:43:16,591
My dad was supportive

859
00:43:16,830 --> 00:43:19,724
even though my mom didn’t agree with that choice.

860
00:43:20,786 --> 00:43:21,461
Dad.

861
00:43:21,461 --> 00:43:21,964
Hmm?

862
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:23,640
I want a tablet.

863
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:27,986
Are you serious about getting into art school?

864
00:43:28,543 --> 00:43:32,350
But later, I didn’t continue my studies because

865
00:43:37,369 --> 00:43:39,385
my dad had an accident.

866
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:45,765
I never picked up the tablet he gave me again.

867
00:43:47,916 --> 00:43:51,343
No wonder you wouldn’t accept my tablet.

868
00:43:52,553 --> 00:43:55,119
I’m sorry.

869
00:43:55,544 --> 00:43:56,230
Hey,

870
00:43:57,133 --> 00:43:58,765
it’s not your fault.

871
00:43:59,296 --> 00:44:00,458
You know what?

872
00:44:01,945 --> 00:44:07,193
Your determination gives me a lot to think about.

873
00:44:08,096 --> 00:44:12,589
I think I’ll get my dad’s tablet fixed.

874
00:44:13,990 --> 00:44:18,830
And I’ve researched what universities in Bangkok offer painting courses.

875
00:44:20,025 --> 00:44:22,863
I think I still have time to submit my portfolio.

876
00:44:24,403 --> 00:44:26,455
You’re going to study in Bangkok?

877
00:44:27,490 --> 00:44:29,118
You have to pass your audition.

878
00:44:29,814 --> 00:44:31,177
New Zealand is far.

879
00:44:32,350 --> 00:44:34,345
Bangkok is as far as I can follow you.

880
00:44:36,815 --> 00:44:37,814
Okay.

881
00:44:38,690 --> 00:44:41,577
Hearing this makes me want to win even more.

882
00:44:42,240 --> 00:44:42,991
Let’s make a promise.

883
00:44:44,903 --> 00:44:45,895
I promise.

884
00:44:58,030 --> 00:44:58,696
Tae.

885
00:45:00,635 --> 00:45:01,863
I’m lonely.

886
00:45:02,447 --> 00:45:03,576
Tae, what’s wrong?

887
00:45:30,052 --> 00:45:31,242
Am I crying?

888
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:33,075
Yes.

889
00:45:34,270 --> 00:45:35,465
Bad dream?

890
00:45:41,493 --> 00:45:42,894
I dreamed that I got to debut,

891
00:45:44,381 --> 00:45:45,779
but no one came to watch me.

892
00:45:47,903 --> 00:45:49,498
No one cared about me.

893
00:45:56,774 --> 00:45:57,787
It’s okay.

894
00:45:58,637 --> 00:46:02,418
If you tell your family, they’ll come to support you.

895
00:46:03,666 --> 00:46:04,948
I’m not sure about that.

896
00:46:06,249 --> 00:46:07,773
They never care about me.

897
00:46:09,446 --> 00:46:10,569
Please don’t leave me.

898
00:46:12,561 --> 00:46:14,357
I’ll go with you to the finish line.

899
00:46:28,581 --> 00:46:31,294
I got so much encouragement from you today.

900
00:46:31,745 --> 00:46:33,758
I’m definitely going to pass the audition tomorrow.

901
00:46:35,033 --> 00:46:35,843
Yeah.

902
00:46:36,135 --> 00:46:37,587
I have something for you.

903
00:46:38,145 --> 00:46:39,080
What is it?

904
00:46:39,770 --> 00:46:40,635
What?

905
00:46:40,980 --> 00:46:41,627
Here.

906
00:46:42,025 --> 00:46:44,255
This is your lucky charm from me.

907
00:46:44,706 --> 00:46:47,053
You made this for me?

908
00:46:48,407 --> 00:46:49,255
Give me your hand.

909
00:46:57,620 --> 00:46:59,938
I just wanted to do something for you too.

910
00:47:03,920 --> 00:47:05,473
This is so cute.

911
00:47:06,031 --> 00:47:08,869
I think you have to bless it.

912
00:47:08,869 --> 00:47:09,963
Otherwise, it won’t be powerful.

913
00:47:10,282 --> 00:47:11,441
Come on. Bless it for me.

914
00:47:16,858 --> 00:47:19,246
A pat ti yae, a pat ti tae tae na.

915
00:47:19,246 --> 00:47:19,904
Abracadabra!

916
00:47:21,179 --> 00:47:22,129
You’re all set.

917
00:47:22,687 --> 00:47:23,609
Seriously?

918
00:47:24,910 --> 00:47:29,078
I think in addition to the blessing, you have to place your magic too.

919
00:47:29,370 --> 00:47:30,216
What?

920
00:47:30,216 --> 00:47:31,186
Place your magic.

921
00:47:31,876 --> 00:47:32,779
What are you doing?

922
00:47:34,777 --> 00:47:37,866
This is how you can place your magic on my face.

923
00:47:40,657 --> 00:47:41,568
Come on.

924
00:47:47,925 --> 00:47:52,587
♪ I know you don’t like if I call you my boo ♪

925
00:47:52,587 --> 00:47:57,604
♪ Then what word can express how much I cherish you ♪

926
00:47:57,604 --> 00:47:58,465
Done.

927
00:47:58,465 --> 00:47:59,995
Go get ‘em.
♪ Maybe I’ll just replace it with your name ♪

928
00:48:00,473 --> 00:48:01,257
I will.

929
00:48:01,257 --> 00:48:02,935
♪ My boo is you, it’s the same ♪

930
00:48:02,935 --> 00:48:08,640
♪ I want to call you boo, but only your name now should do ♪

931
00:48:20,800 --> 00:48:23,433
(Here comes the day I go after my dream.)

932
00:48:23,433 --> 00:48:24,213
Go get ‘em.

933
00:48:24,213 --> 00:48:25,266
I’m rooting for you.

934
00:48:25,425 --> 00:48:27,408
I got here because of you, Kang.

935
00:48:27,408 --> 00:48:28,816
I think we’ll definitely pass.

936
00:48:29,028 --> 00:48:29,855
Trust me.

937
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,606
How long have you been crushing on him?

938
00:48:31,606 --> 00:48:32,835
Nonsense.

939
00:48:32,835 --> 00:48:34,245
You’re going to get it from me.

940
00:48:34,590 --> 00:48:36,368
I’m here for you.

941
00:48:37,921 --> 00:48:39,068
Which Moo is cuter?

942
00:48:40,422 --> 00:48:41,781
Can I hit on you?

943
00:48:42,392 --> 00:48:44,585
Kang, do you love me?

944
00:48:46,231 --> 00:48:47,240
Will you be my boyfriend?

945
00:48:47,710 --> 00:48:50,294
(Just you wait, I’m getting a boyfriend!)

